SECURITY.md
     1→# Security Policy
     2→
     3→To report a security vulnerability, please use the
     4→[Tidelift security contact](https://tidelift.com/security).
     5→Tidelift will coordinate the fix and disclosure.
docs/deprecated.md
     1→# Deprecated
     2→
     3→These features are deprecated, which means they may go away in a future major version of Commander.
     4→They are currently still available for backwards compatibility, but should not be used in new code.
    22→### RegExp .option() parameter
    23→
    24→The `.option()` method allowed a RegExp as the third parameter to restrict what values were accepted.
    34→### noHelp
    35→
    36→This was an option passed to `.command()` to hide the command from the built-in help:
    44→### Callback to .help() and .outputHelp()
    45→
    46→These routines allowed a callback parameter to process the built-in help before display.
    62→### .on('--help')
    63→
    64→This was the way to add custom help after the built-in help. From Commander v3.0.0 this used the custom long help option flags, if changed.
    87→### .on('command:*')
    88→
    89→This was emitted when the command argument did not match a known subcommand (as part of the implementation of `.command('*')`).
    98→### .command('*')
    99→
   100→This was used to add a default command to the program.
   118→### cmd.description(cmdDescription, argDescriptions)
   119→
   120→This was used to add command argument descriptions for the help.
   141→### InvalidOptionArgumentError
   142→
   143→This was used for throwing an error from custom option processing, for a nice error message.
   171→### Import from `commander/esm.mjs`
   172→
   173→The first support for named imports required an explicit entry file.
   187→### cmd._args
   188→
   189→This was always private, but was previously the only way to access the command `Argument` array.
   203→### .addHelpCommand(string|boolean|undefined)
   204→
   205→This was originally used with a variety of parameters, but not by passing a Command object despite the "add" name.
   227→## Removed
   228→
   229→### Short option flag longer than a single character
   230→
   231→Short option flags like `-ws` were never supported, but the old README did not make this clear. The README now states that short options are a single character.
   238→### Default import of global Command object
   239→
   240→The default import was a global Command object.
docs/help-in-depth.md
     1→# Help in Depth
     2→
     3→The built-in help is formatted using the Help class.
     4→You can configure the Help behaviour by modifying data properties and methods using `.configureHelp()`, or by subclassing using `.createHelp()` if you prefer.
    20→## Data Properties
    21→
    22→The data properties are:
    34→## Stringify and Style
    35→
    36→The `Help` object has narrowly focused methods to allow customising the displayed help.
   118→## Layout
   119→
   120→Utility methods which control the layout include `padWidth`, `boxWrap`, and `formatItem`. These can be overridden to change the layout or replace with an alternative implementation.
docs/options-in-depth.md
     2→# Options in Depth
     3→
     4→The README covers declaring and using options, and mostly parsing will work the way you and your users expect. This page covers some special cases
     5→and subtle issues in depth.
    15→## Options taking varying numbers of option-arguments
    16→
    17→Certain options take a varying number of arguments:
    30→### Parsing ambiguity
    31→
    32→There is a potential downside to be aware of. If a command has both
    33→command-arguments and options with varying option-arguments, this introduces a parsing ambiguity which may affect the user of your program.
    34→Commander looks for option-arguments first, but the user may
    35→intend the argument following the option as a command or command-argument.
    79→#### Alternative: Make `--` part of your syntax
    80→
    81→Rather than trying to teach your users what `--` does, you could just make it part of your syntax.
   104→#### Alternative: Put options last
   105→
   106→Commander follows the GNU convention for parsing and allows options before or after the command-arguments, or intermingled.
   107→So by putting the options last, the command-arguments do not get confused with the option-arguments.
   126→#### Alternative: Use options instead of command-arguments
   127→
   128→This is a bit more radical, but completely avoids the parsing ambiguity!
   148→## Combining short options, and options taking arguments
   149→
   150→Multiple boolean short options can be combined after a single `-`, like `ls -al`. You can also include just
   151→a single short option which might take a value, as any following characters will
   152→be taken as the value.
   191→### Combining short options as if boolean
   192→
   193→Before Commander v5, combining a short option and the value was not supported, and combined short flags were always expanded.
   194→So `-avl` expanded to `-a -v -l`.
docs/parsing-and-hooks.md
     1→# Parsing life cycle and hooks
     2→
     3→The processing starts with an array of args. Each command processes and removes the options it understands, and passes the remaining args to the next subcommand.
     4→The final command calls the action handler.
docs/release-policy.md
     1→# Release Policy
     2→
     3→We follow [Semantic Versioning](http://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html), and limit breaking changes to major versions.
docs/terminology.md
     1→# Terminology
     2→
     3→The command line arguments are made up of options, option-arguments, commands, and command-arguments.
docs/zh-CN/不再推荐使用的功能.md
     1→# 不再推荐使用的功能
     2→
     3→本文中列出的功能不再推荐使用。它们在 Commander 未来的主要版本（major version）中可能被移除。为保证后向兼容，这些功能目前还可以使用，但它们不应被用在新代码中。
    18→## .option() 方法的正则表达式参数
    19→
    20→`.option()`方法可以接受一个正则表达式作为第三个参数，以规定可以接受的选项参数值。
    30→## noHelp
    31→
    32→此选项曾被用作传入`.command()`方法，以在内建的帮助信息中隐藏该命令：
    40→## 默认导入的全局 Command 对象
    41→
    42→Commander 的默认导入曾是一个全局的`Command`对象。
    61→## .help() 与 .outputHelp() 的回调函数参数
    62→
    63→这两个方法曾允许传入一个回调函数，以在展示前处理帮助信息。
    79→## .on('--help')
    80→
    81→此功能曾被用作在内建的帮助信息后输出自定义的帮助信息。自 Commander v3.0.0 起，如果有自定义的帮助选项，则此方法使用该自定义的帮助选项。
   104→## .on('command:*')
   105→
   106→当命令参数与已知子命令不匹配时发出此消息（作为 `.command('')` 实现的一部分）。
   114→## .command('*')
   115→
   116→这用于向程序添加默认命令。
   134→## cmd.description(cmdDescription, argDescriptions)
   135→
   136→此功能曾用来为命令参数添加描述信息。
   157→## InvalidOptionArgumentError
   158→
   159→此类曾被用来在自定义选项处理中抛出错误，以显示错误信息。
   187→## 短选项标志长于单个字符
   188→
   189→短选项从未支持像 `-ws` 的标识，但旧的 README 并没有明确说明这一点。README 现在声明短选项是单个字符。
docs/zh-CN/可变参数的选项.md
     1→# 可变参数的选项
     2→
     3→README 文档介绍了选项的声明与使用。大多数情况下，选项的解析行为，与您和您程序用户的期望相符。本文将详述一些特殊用例和细节问题。
    26→## 解析中的歧义
    27→
    28→解析选项时，有一些潜在的问题值得注意。当一个命令既有命令参数，又有选项的时候，在解析过程中有可能出现歧义。这可能会影响用户使用您的程序。
    73→### 方案一：让`--`成为语法的一部分
    74→
    75→与其让用户理解`--`的用法，您也可以直接把它作为程序语法的一部分。
    98→### 方案二：把选项放在最后
    99→
   100→Commander 遵循 GNU 解析命令的惯例，允许选项出现在命令参数之前或者之后，也可以将选项和命令参数相互穿插。
   120→### 方案三：使用选项替代命令参数
   121→
   122→这个方案虽然有点激进，但是可以完美避免解析中的歧义。
   142→## 合并短选项和带有参数的选项
   143→
   144→多个 boolean 型的短选项可以合并起来写在同一个`-`号后面，比如`ls -al`。同时，你也可以在其中包括一个接受参数的短选项，此时，任何跟在其后的字符都将被视作这个选项的值。
   183→### 将短选项视作 boolean 类型选项合并
   184→
   185→在 Commander v5 之前，并不支持合并短选项和值。合并的 boolean 类型选项会被展开。
docs/zh-CN/术语表.md
     1→# 术语表
     2→
     3→命令行参数由选项（options）、选项参数（option-arguments）、命令（commands），以及命令参数（command-arguments）组成。
